The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               Infocom Snippets
                  
	Calcutta, Jan. 15: The State Bank of India today said it would increase its IT budget in 2009-10 to Rs 1,250 crore.    
	We are spending Rs 1,000 crore in IT this financial year. This will be raised by at least 25 per cent next fiscal, said R.P. Sinha, deputy MD (IT), at Infocom 08-09.         
	Calcutta: Consumer electronics major Samsung has said it would concentrate on rural and semi-urban areas for growth. Rural India is almost untapped and we need to concentrate on markets in the rural and semi-urban places, said Sunil Dutt, head (mobile business), at Infocom.
                                                                                                                                                                       
